Plotting expression levels

Jared J. Homola

4/19/2020

This document ideas for plotting gene/transcript expression levels. It goes through transcript-level expression plots, but gene-level would be the same idea. The example given is for the day 1 control, low, moderate, and high shedding birds.

Plot expression of a cluster

Gray lines are individual transcripts and the blue line is their mean value. This is for just one tissue type- the one that is used to build heatmaps and establish groupings (ileum in this case).
